{"TopicId":153937,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"We Want More Space Sensors!","CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T02:02:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T02:02:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.space.com/35097-missile-defense-tracking-systems-in-space.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.space.com/35097-missile-defense-tracking-systems-in-space.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T15:14:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOtherwise\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022v-0011.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022750\u0022 src=\u0022https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-hhSyhuP4UjA/Tfx5MoC9kjI/AAAAAAAACVA/KiNfhyopZPo/s1600/v-0011.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022907\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T15:18:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be quite a waste to have all these laser sats and drones up there and hopefully never actually being used for anything except deterrent. As long as they\u0027re up there, how about using them for debris removal via laser ablation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T19:09:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Amazing\u0022ly, the russians have done it for a few decades. Impossible if the US haven\u0027t got one of it\u0027s own yet. Here\u0027s \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/EKS_(satellite_system)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Etheir latest.\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T22:02:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure we need more space sensors, but they should be pointed up, not down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used to frequent space.com, but then they decided to just shut down the forums without notice or explanation. Now they deal with fearmongering.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSDC, going downhill since 2011.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-24T22:03:04Z\u0022 title=\u002212/24/2016 10:03  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 24, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Shpaget\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Elthy","CreatedById":63317,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-24T22:09:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou dont want an effective missile defense system. Luckily its also more or less impossible to build an effective one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you dont have to fear a counter attack for a nuclear first strike nothing is keeping you from nuking your enemy whenever you want....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-25T16:53:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably good opportunities for training and evaluation too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222899628\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482592734\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/24/2016 at 9:18 AM, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be quite a waste to have all these laser sats and drones up there and hopefully never actually being used for anything except deterrent. As long as they\u0027re up there, how about using them for debris removal via laser ablation?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222900056\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482617397\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263317\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Elthy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 hours ago, Elthy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou dont want an effective missile defense system. Luckily its also more or less impossible to build an effective one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you dont have to fear a counter attack for a nuclear first strike nothing is keeping you from nuking your enemy whenever you want....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with MAD is that while it works for humanity as a whole, there is still incentive for the individual state to develop missile defense.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonfliesgoats","CreatedById":168077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T07:10:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222900052\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153937\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482616956\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002245577\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Shpaget\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/24/2016 at 10:02 PM, Shpaget said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSure we need more space sensors, but they should be pointed up, not down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI used to frequent space.com, but then they decided to just shut down the forums without notice or explanation. Now they deal with fearmongering.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSDC, going downhill since 2011.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInteresting. \u00A0I haven\u0027t really thought\u00A0about how Space.com has changed its tenor over time, but it does seem to have changed. \u00A0Fear makes good click bait. \u00A0I know I take the hook more often than I should.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"John22","CreatedById":172771,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T07:15:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#000000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;\u0022\u003EThe sensors used in satellites are specific based on the applications they are used for. However there are some generic sensors that are common for all the man made satellites.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;\u0022\u003E1. Attitude sensors (to determine its position and directivity since only stars could be used as fixed points)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;\u0022\u003E2. Star tracker sensors (to detect the orientation of the craft)\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr style=\u0022margin-bottom:0px;color:rgb(51,51,51);font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027q_serif\u0027, Georgia, Times, \u0027Times New Roman\u0027, serif;font-size:15px;font-style:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;\u0022\u003E3. Temperature sensor (as the temperature highly fluctuates during the time of facing the sun and while on the shadow of earth this temp sensors are one of the must have sensors)\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-indent:0px;float:none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cfont color=\u0022#000000\u0022 face=\u0022q_serif, Georgia, Times, Times New Roman, serif\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:15px;\u0022\u003EFor the defenses, we require more Space-based senses\u00A0so that the sensors could detect missiles or any type\u00A0of space threats. More sensor\u00A0means more eyes on the target.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/font\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-28T07:16:54Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2016 07:16  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by John22\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}